# Task
I need a script to check select PATonline files to sort out what is being used as the username to assist with processing later.
It should -
1. Prompt user for files. Use dog_box
2. Ask user for expected ID format.
These will be one of the following ABC0001, 182815548 or 5548.
With the numeric ID the could be 2 digits bigger or smaller, but will never have alphas in them. They may be stored as a number or a string.
With the ALPHAnumeric on it will always be 2 letters, then another letter or a - then 4 numbers.
Ask the user to choose via a dialog box. It will only ever be one of them.
3. Check the data in the user name column.
 if all values in the user name column of a file match, move the file to [output_folder]/Expected_ID/{filename}
if not
[output_folder]/Files_to_check/{filename}

Ask any questions you need to assist.